page.title: 14Greenhead.
page.content: First it was called Stable Row then it was called Long Row, now it is known as Greenhead.There used to be more than the one row of houses and the row that is left starts at number 22, finishing at number 42 a total of 20 houses.The houses are all terraced apart from one or individual farm cottages nearby. There are no shops or facilities of any kind apart from a playing field. The nearest shops are either in Howden or at Crook. There used to be a railway line running past the houses and some of the track can still be seen.The roads are all rough tracks although it is planned to build a smooth road up to Beechburn Farm.
